  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a prospective cohort study to examine the efficacy of ESMR application in patients
      with refractory angina despite optimal medical therapy, not suitable for further PCI or CABG.
      Characteristics such as angina class scores (CCS class score), nitroglycerin consumption and
      hospitalization were compared at baseline and 1, 6 and 12 months after ESMR therapy. The
      effect on cardiac perfusion was assessed at 6 months.
    </textblock>
