  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  history of coronary artery disease;

          -  refractory angina pectoris, defined as the persistence of a angina pectoris (Canadian
             Cardiovascular Society class ≥ 2) for more than 3 months, despite the use of optimal
             medical therapy (which included β blockers, calcium channel blockers, long-acting
             nitrates, ivabradine, ranolazine and trimetazidine, up-titrated to the maximal
             tolerated dose) and coronary disease not amenable for further revascularization (as
             determined by an interventional cardiologist and cardiac surgeon);

          -  stable maximal medical therapy for at least 6 weeks;

          -  stress-induced ischemia at baseline SPECT;

          -  left ventricular ejection fraction higher than 40%;

          -  age higher than 18 years.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  myocardial infarction or unstable angina in the previous 3 months,

          -  acute myocarditis, pericarditis, left ventricular thrombus, cardiac malignancies,
             chronic pulmonary disease (including emphysema and pulmonary fibrosis), endocarditis

          -  pregnancy
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
